My guess it is in the progressbar but to be sure I don't forget open an issue as a reminder.

```
blueman-manager 10.54.24 DEBUG    Base:58 do_g_properties_changed: /org/bluez/hci0 {'Discovering': False}
/usr/lib/python3.8/site-packages/gi/overrides/GObject.py:502: Warning: ../glib/gobject/gsignal.c:2735: instance '0x559112929120' has no handler with id '10802'
  return func(*args, **kwargs)
```

As in title, Blueman freezes when connecting/disconnecting Sixaxis DS3. I'm using Arch/Manjaro and I tried git version and stable 2.0 version. When I have enabled Bluetooth and I press the "PS" button, the gamepad automatically connects and it works, but blueman-applet and/or blueman-manager always freezes, and I must kill the processes. The same about disconnect - the blueman-manager freezes, but not always.

//Edit: Can't pair on first gamepad connection using blueman. I must use bluetoothctl and write a few commands from https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Sony_DualShock#DualShock_3.
Bluedevil from KDE4 also pairs automatically and it doesn't freeze on Sixaxis DS3.

uname -a:
Linux raspberrypi 3.12.28+ #713 PREEMPT Fri Sep 19 16:43:32 BST 2014 armv6l GNU/Linux

Blueman applet 1.22

Hi,
My problem is that I need to know the given IP on my tablet(cannot see it on my tablet). When enable NAP on Local Services "dhcpd3" is greyed-out ,even if I install "isc-dhcp-server".
My only option is "dnsmasq". If I install "dnsmasq-base" then on syslog I see that blueman overrides my dnsmasq.conf settings :eg "dhcp-range=10.1.1.50,10.1.1.50" and gives an unknown IP which I cannot see.

